chilipepper <p>For chili syntax, <code>function</code>, <code>return</code>, <code>raise</code> are keywords.</p> <pre><code>f: function(param1, param2, ...) {
  statement;
  statement;
  return value;
  raise "error";
  ...
};
</code></pre> <p>Single quotation <code>'</code> is used for creating a column expression.</p> <p>For pepper syntax, <code>:</code> is used to return a value from a function, <code>raise</code> is used to raise an error.</p> <pre><code>f: {[param1; param2; ...]
  statement;
  statement;
  :value;
  raise "error";
  ...
};
</code></pre>

chilipepper <pre><code>f(arg1, arg2, ...);
</code></pre> <pre><code>f[arg1; arg2; ...];
</code></pre>

